<br>
Other than this only thing I can tell you is try the bazaar/SH. Your prices nor lag won't be as good but I suppose you don't have to bother with doing a lowbie quest to get faction up. /shrug Bad thing about SH is half of SH DOES require you to do quests to raise faction and some of the molds you'll need are sold there. So maybe doing a lowbie quest isn't so bad? lol <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udatulmidgetchomper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Datul Midgetchomper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#E9D756>(10/9/02 7:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=272.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: little help with Smithing maybe? :)</span><hr size=1> One of the ogurs in Feerott sells the banded molds if you wanna start out there.  Mugu by name.  <br>
